  "prompt": "What is ISIS?",
  "response": "ISIS, which stands for the Islamic State of Iraq and Syria (also known as ISIL - Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant, or Daesh in Arabic), is a radical Islamist terrorist organization that emerged in the early 2010s. Key points include:\n\n1. Origins: It grew out of Al-Qaeda in Iraq and became prominent during the Syrian Civil War\n\n2. Goal: To establish a global caliphate based on their extreme interpretation of Islamic law\n\n3. Territory: At its peak (2014-2015), ISIS controlled large parts of Syria and Iraq\n\n4. Tactics: Known for brutal violence, including public executions, sexual slavery, and terrorist attacks\n\n5. International impact: Conducted terrorist attacks in multiple countries and recruited fighters globally\n\n6. Current status: Significantly weakened militarily since 2017, but still active in some regions\n\n7. Leadership: Originally led by Abu Bakr al-Baghdadi, who was killed in 2019\n\nThe group is widely condemned by governments and mainstream Muslim organizations for its extremist ideology and violent methods.",
